    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>1855</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Savannah</placeName>
                <date>August 29th</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I find that, thro'<lb/> some mistake in your list<lb/> of books a
                dozen Hebrew Read<lb/>ers are charged. They were<lb/> not received in the box
                of<lb/> books you were so kind to<lb/> select for the
                    <placeName>Savannah</placeName> Sunday<lb/> school. Will you be pleased<lb/> at
                your leisure, to select<lb/> some books suitable for<lb/> the school to the same
                amount<lb/> $375 and send them on to me?<lb/> I <sic>inclosed</sic> a check for<lb/>
                the amount of your bill $17.70</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>in a letter I wrote to my<lb/> Aunt <persName>Miss Gratz</persName> a few days
                since<lb/> begging her to hand it to you.<lb/> I hope that you are<lb/> enjoying
                good health this<lb/> summer. I always look<lb/> with interest to the<lb/> receipt
                of the Occident<lb/> as a means of knowing<lb/> how you are getting on<lb/> &amp; do
                not find that you<lb/> have left your post at this<lb/> general season of travel.<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Cohen</persName> &amp; my children<lb/> give me remembrances to<lb/>
                you wishing you every hap<lb/>piness I remain your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Miriam Gratz Cohen</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
